Moving to Lisbon has really changed my life. I’ve learned what it means to pour love into myself. I’ve learned that loving yourself is not only feeling good in your skin but connecting with yourself thru your emotions. It’s choosing to treat every unique part of me with love. Even in the moments that I dont feel good. Allowing myself to feel everything as it comes and holding myself thru it. Spending time with myself and appreciating every stage of my life as it is. Because it’s all just mine 🌸

I believe we are here to learn thru these emotions that our body is experiencing. And when you fully surrendor to yourself, the life you desire creates itself around you without needing to work so hard for it. There is so much power in changing your perspective to knowing everything you’re going thru is there to serve you. Because when you allow yourself to feel everything without it being bad, over time you start feeling your own cup getting fuller. And the need to seek whatever you feel you’re lacking, goes away and life gets so meaningful. 

So if you’re going thru something, keep having hope, and realise that you are incontrol of how you precieve it. Sit in it and realise it is only a doorway for you to reach your highest potential. Give yourself grace 🌸
Be gentle to yourself and let go of the shame you carry from the past. Ask yourself, what do I need to feel better and then take action towards your own wellbeing. Because by doing that, you are able to inspire and connect with others from a place of love. It is such a beautiful process to learn about yourself 🌸You are so worthy and beautiful as you are right now 🌸

latestPosts.caption:
I’ve been ”unemployed” for almost a year now, and it was hands down the best decision I’ve made. I don’t believe we are meant to be living to work. The whole concept only creates more lack. Focusing on myself, my needs and nurturing my creativity has brought me more opportunities, abundance and joy, then working a 9-5 ever did. Realising, that I in fact am the creator of my own reality and through practising inner work I’ve been able to shift my reality complitely. Focusing on turning my skills into money and not my time. 

Life only brings you exactly what you believe you’re worthy of, so be mindful and get in tune with yourself. Notice, what are the limiting beliefs, stories about your identity and emotional package you keep holding on to, that keep you in the cycle of exhaustion. You can’t expect different results without different action. And most times it requires you to jump into the unknown, a place where nothing is ”certain”. But remember, stability does not equal a blueprint. Let go of the control and see how life opens up to you 🦋 

#mindsetshifting #innerworkcoach #realityshift #explore #lawofattractioninaction #ratrace #selfmadewoman #intuitiveliving #slowliving #abundancemindset
